{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017PRSkx2YLCr5Yoe98Y7Rkc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture:\n\n1. The `copy-cookie` initContainer reads from the `rabbitmq-cookie-perpod` Secret and copies the per-pod key to `/var/lib/rabbitmq/.erlang.cookie`\n2. The secret has:\n   - `rabbitmq-0`: `supersecretcookie` (base64: `c3VwZXJzZWNyZXRjb29raWU=`)\n   - `rabbitmq-1`: `supersecretcookie` (base64: `c3VwZXJzZWNyZXRjb29raWU=`)\n   - `rabbitmq-2`: `driftedcookie` (base64: `ZHJpZnRlZGNvb2tpZQ==`)\n\nTo fix this, I need to patch the `rabbitmq-cookie-perpod` secret to update `rabbitmq-2`'s cookie to match the others, then restart that pod so the initContainer picks up the corrected value and the node can rejoin the cluster.\n\nThe tricky part is that `rabbitmq-2` has already booted as a standalone node with the wrong cookie, so its Mnesia database contains state reflecting that isolated startup. When it restarts with the correct cookie, the peer discovery plugin should attempt to find and join the cluster, but the PVC still holds the old Mnesia data from when it was running standalone. I need to account for this Mnesia state when the pod comes back up.\n\nLet me check how peer discovery is configured in the rabbitmq.conf to understand what happens during the rejoin process.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4146,"cache_read_input_tokens":31302,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4146},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"74bcabbf-73b1-473e-915e-35ec1e2a46c3","uuid":"6ba8a65b-8fa0-4824-8364-cf99592b93d5","request_id":"req_011CcRKsKvq1zEBVVJQFXpt9"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017PRSkx2YLCr5Yoe98Y7Rkc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I understand the full picture. The `copy-cookie` initContainer reads per-pod keys from the secret — `rabbitmq-2` was given `driftedcookie` instead of `supersecretcookie`, so it started as a standalone node with its own Mnesia database. Let me check the RabbitMQ config and then fix the cookie."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4146,"cache_read_input_tokens":31302,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4146},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"74bcabbf-73b1-473e-915e-35ec1e2a46c3","uuid":"eb32991f-957d-4257-888a-2e5c7e534b45","request_id":"req_011CcRKsKvq1zEBVVJQFXpt9"}
